#compdef dobi
# =============================================================================
# dobi — Daniel Nephin's "A build automation tool for
#          Docker applications" — a Go-implemented
#          declarative task runner that orchestrates
#          Docker-based build workflows by composing
#          resources (images, mounts, env-files, jobs,
#          aliases, networks, volumes, computed-config,
#          composed-actions) declared in `dobi.yaml`
#          into a DAG of typed-action invocations
#          (build → image, run → job, attach → mount,
#          etc.) which the dobi engine dispatches to
#          the Docker Engine API for execution.
#          Distinguishing from Make (no native Docker
#          awareness; reinvents Docker primitives via
#          shell-out), docker-compose (focused on
#          long-running multi-container services, not
#          one-shot build tasks), Bazel (heavyweight
#          hermetic build system; steep learning
#          curve), Earthly (Earthfile-based; alternative
#          syntax; commercial cloud tier), and direct
#          docker-build shell scripts (no dependency
#          graph, no caching) by:
#            - RESOURCE[:ACTION] SYNTAX — invoke a
#              task as `dobi <resource>[:<action>]`;
#              e.g. `dobi build` runs the default
#              action of the `build` resource;
#              `dobi build:push` runs the explicit
#              `push` action.  Multiple
#              RESOURCE:ACTION targets can be passed
#              and run in dependency order
#            - DECLARATIVE YAML CONFIG — every project
#              has a `dobi.yaml` declaring its
#              resources + their dependencies; users
#              never write imperative Docker scripts
#            - GO-DOCKERCLIENT FOUNDATION — uses
#              fsouza/go-dockerclient v1.6 (this is
#              the headline CLI library that CONTINUES
#              Axis 44 on the Go side; see taxonomy
#              notes below) for all Docker Engine API
#              operations: image build/pull/push,
#              container create/start/stop/wait,
#              volume mount, network create
#            - TYPED RESOURCE MODEL — each resource
#              has a type (`image`/`run`/`mount`/`env-
#              file`/`job`/`alias`/`network`/`volume`/
#              `compose`/`computed-config`) with type-
#              specific configuration keys + actions;
#              dobi typechecks the YAML against
#              github.com/dnephin/configtf at config-
#              load time so syntax errors are caught
#              before execution
#            - BIND-MOUNT vs LAYER-INJECTION — the
#              `--no-bind-mount` flag (or
#              DOBI_NO_BIND_MOUNT env-var) switches
#              from default bind-mounting of host
#              directories into containers to BAKING
#              the mount content as an image layer.
#              Useful for CI environments where
#              bind-mounts are unavailable or
#              undesirable
#            - TAG-BASED FILTERING — `dobi list -t
#              <tag1,tag2>` filters task listing to
#              resources matching the given tag(s);
#              `dobi list -g` groups them by tag.
#              Useful for projects with many tasks
#              + multiple personas (CI, dev,
#              integration, smoke)
#            - DOCKER_API_VERSION OVERRIDE — sets via
#              env-var; defaults to API 1.25 (Docker
#              1.13+).  Lets dobi connect to older
#              Docker daemons (e.g. embedded systems
#              with pinned Docker versions)
#            - GIT INTEGRATION via gogits/git-module
#              — dobi can query git metadata
#              (current branch, commit hash, tag) at
#              task time + use it in image tags or
#              environment variables.  Avoids the
#              "shell out to git for tag" pattern
#              common in Make-based Dockerfile flows
#            - CONFIGTF TYPE-CHECKED YAML — uses
#              Daniel Nephin's own configtf library
#              (github.com/dnephin/configtf) which
#              performs Go-struct-tag-based YAML
#              validation; reports typos in
#              resource names + invalid action
#              combinations with line numbers
#            - LOGRUS LOGGING — uses sirupsen/logrus
#              v1.4 for structured logging; `-v`
#              raises level to Debug; `-q` raises
#              to Warn.  Stderr destination by
#              default; custom logging.Formatter
#              produces dobi-styled output
#            - LIST + AUTOCLEAN SUBCOMMANDS —
#              `dobi list` enumerates declared
#              resources + descriptions; `dobi
#              autoclean` invokes the `remove`
#              action across every resource that
#              defines one, recovering disk space
#              after a build run
#            - 315+ STARS ON dnephin/dobi — well-
#              regarded in the Docker tooling
#              community; backed by Daniel Nephin's
#              decade-long Docker open-source track
#              record at Docker Inc (docker-compose
#              v2 + buildkit maintainer)
#          Used by: teams running multi-stage Docker-
#          based build pipelines who want a typed
#          replacement for Makefile-driven Docker
#          orchestration, CI/CD environments that
#          benefit from dobi's caching + dependency
#          graph + declarative resource model, and
#          developers who prefer YAML + cobra-CLI
#          ergonomics over BASH-driven docker-compose
#          extension dances.
#
# Author:  Daniel Nephin (dnephin on GitHub); based
#          in Toronto.  Long-time Docker contributor
#          (docker-compose v2 + buildkit maintainer
#          at Docker Inc).
# Source:  https://github.com/dnephin/dobi
#          https://github.com/dnephin/dobi/blob/master/main.go
#          https://github.com/dnephin/dobi/blob/master/cmd/dobi.go
#          https://github.com/dnephin/dobi/blob/master/cmd/list.go
#          https://github.com/dnephin/dobi/blob/master/cmd/autoclean.go
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; `dobi --help`
#          shows cobra-generated subcommand list;
#          `dobi <sub> --help` per-subcommand options.
#          Full docs in repo docs/.
# Library: github.com/fsouza/go-dockerclient v1.6.4
#          (Francisco Souza's "Go client for the
#          Docker Engine API" — predates the official
#          docker/docker/client library and remains
#          popular for its synchronous-ish API +
#          back-compat with older Docker daemons).
#          This is the headline dependency for this
#          completion's axis-44 continuation role;
#          see taxonomy notes below.  Also github.com/
#          docker/docker (Docker Engine types, used
#          transitively for type aliases), spf13/cobra
#          (Axis 1 argparse), sirupsen/logrus (Axis 9
#          logging), dnephin/configtf (typed-YAML
#          config validation; Daniel's own library),
#          dnephin/go-os-user (cross-platform user
#          lookup), gogits/git-module (git metadata),
#          golang/mock (test mocking), google/go-cmp
#          (test comparison).
# License: Apache-2.0
# Status:  315+ stars on dnephin/dobi; maintained
#          (latest commit 2026-01-12); version 0.15.0;
#          mature in terms of API stability but not
#          rapid feature development.
#
