# apocas/dockerode user to close Axis 44 at 1/1/1.
#
# WHY fsouza/go-dockerclient IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-
# 44 CONTINUATION:
#
#   github.com/fsouza/go-dockerclient by Francisco
#   Souza is the de-facto third-party Go Docker
#   Engine API client, predating Docker's own
#   official Go client (docker/docker/client) and
#   continuing to be widely used for its smaller
#   API surface + back-compat with older Docker
#   daemons.  Distinguishing characteristics:
#     1. THIRD-PARTY ESTABLISHED BEFORE OFFICIAL —
#        Francisco Souza started this library in
#        2013, before Docker Inc shipped their
#        official Go client.  Many established Go
#        Docker tools were built against it and
#        haven't migrated
#     2. SYNCHRONOUS-ISH API — operations return
#        results synchronously by default (e.g.
#        `client.ListContainers()`); streams + log-
#        tail are async via callback channels.
#        Simpler than the official docker/docker/
#        client's pure-async API surface
#     3. SMALLER DEPENDENCY GRAPH — go-dockerclient
#        avoids pulling in the entire docker/docker
#        module (which itself depends on many
#        runtime/networking pieces).  Smaller go.mod
#        footprint + faster build
#     4. BACK-COMPAT — supports older Docker API
#        versions (down to 1.14) via API-version
#        negotiation; useful for tools targeting
#        embedded systems or air-gapped CI
#     5. STREAMING SUPPORT — `client.Logs()` streams
#        container logs to an io.Writer;
#        `client.AttachToContainer()` provides
#        bidirectional stdin/stdout/stderr streams
#     6. EVENTS API — `client.AddEventListener()`
#        receives Docker daemon events (container
#        create/start/stop/die, image pull/push,
#        network connect/disconnect, volume mount)
#        on a channel.  Powers tools like docker-
#        gen + logspout
#     7. ~4,000+ STARS ON fsouza/go-dockerclient
#     8. ECOSYSTEM-DOMINANT for THIRD-PARTY TOOLS —
#        used by ctop (top-like container metrics;
#        already in corpus), logspout (log routing;
#        in corpus), ofelia (cron for Docker; in
#        corpus), docker-gen (nginx-proxy file
#        generation; in corpus), kompose (k8s
#        manifest generator; in corpus), dexec (in
#        this same Axis 44 candidate list), dobi
#        (this completion), and many other early-
#        2010s-era Go Docker tools
#
